  "response": "Travancore was a princely state in the southeastern part of Kerala, India. Today, the region that once constituted Travancore is part of the modern Indian state of Kerala. Key cities within this region include Thiruvananthapuram (the state capital), Kollam, Alappuzha, Kottayam, and Pathanamthitta. The area is known for its rich cultural heritage and historical significance.",
